race.comment: REIGN IN THE CASH (7) is a lightly raced galloper who improved sharply at big odds second-up when placed at Gawler. This is easier and fitter again. Looks very well placed in this line-up. MACHINE MAN (5) has started twice and also ran a much better race last time. This is a lesser maiden and has good upside, especially with the blinkers added. HASTA LA WIZARD (4) got home late last time and the start prior was close to the winner. Long overdue but has had 23 tries without success now. FLYING SHELBY (13) was fair fresh when midfield over the border. Suited by the extra ground and did run some goos races over this journey when first moved south from Queensland. Fitter and can improve sharply second-up.
